 The incident occurred in the early hours of Friday, July 26. The multi-vehicle collision happened between the Middelburg Toll Plaza and the weighbridge. The crash claimed three lives and left one in a critical state. Sizwe Bafana Nene (32), Sello Joseph Monama (34) and Johannes Sibiya (25) lost their lives in the crash when they were on their way from eMalahleni to Hendrina
Mr Nene’s funeral will be held in Hendrina on Sunday, Mr Sibiya will be buried in Verena on Saturday. Mr Monama’s family was unavailable for comment before print.       One dead in early morning crash Fake notes in Belfast leads to two arrests Theft of motor vehicles on the rise Accident claims the life of an infant • Save our standby number (072 248 3855) and send us a WhatsApp message with the words “Add me” to be added to our broadcast list. • Like us on Facebook, follow us on Twitter and Instagram. • Subscribe to our YouTube channel. • Click on the link to subscribe to our bi-weekly newsletter via email. Contact our news room on our 24 hr standby number 072 248 3855, or send a mail to our editor tobie@mobserver.co.za